<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n11017c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n11" href="#n11017c">N11 (VI.B.5)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n11all.htm#n11017c"> 17(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> A Prayer = SP / Breastplate </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: &lsquo;St Patrick&apos;s Breastplate&rsquo; is an early Irish incantation attributed to St Patrick by the <cite>Book of Armagh</cite>. It is also known variously as the <cite>Lorica</cite> and the <cite>Faeth Fiada</cite> (interpreted as the &lsquo;Deer&apos;s Cry&rsquo;). It begins: &ldquo;Christ be with me, Christ be before me, Christ be after me, Christ be above me&rdquo;. See Joyce&apos;s letter to Miss Weaver, dated 7 October 1924 (<cite>Letters</cite> 3, 108) for a description of a version of it given to him by his sister-in-law. The Breastplate forms the basis of <ul class="list-inline" id="n11017c"><li>FW 500.12-14. </li><li><a href="../../flex/rA/lexrA.htm#n11017c">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/rA/l39rA.htm#n11017c">1939</a> </mm></li> </ul> </dd></dl>
